import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['lat'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='lat')
    plt.axvline(data['lat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['lat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Lat')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of lat?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
